social_posts.post_text:
It’s true! Are you and your partner total opposites too?

Here’s a short list of examples…

He hates hot food/drinks. I love all the hot dishes & coffee!

He loves socks. I hate them.

He is calm & cool. I am bubbly & action base.

He loves watching movies. I love being productive.

Tag your partner if you are total opposites, but wouldn’t want it any other way!

What’s a typical day like?

It’s drastically different from the 8-4 grind teaching I used to follow and Jeff did the 7-3 grind teaching, then worked his other two jobs. We used to be ships passing. 

It wasn’t working for us. 
We knew we wanted to change this grind. 

So we did just that with communication, some struggle, vision and work.

So many ask, what do your days look like now since you both left teacher & work your own businesses?
They look like this…

Start the morning moving your body. We love working out together. It used to be our only time we would see each other.
Next, once the boys are at school it’s time to go over the day & activities ahead for that night.
With the second cup of coffee in hand, I get to work in the office, Jeff heads up to the bonus room where he offices out of. Sharing an office did not work for us

We then have lunch, mastermind some ideas out about my business & his.
In the afternoon I focus on my team activities with mentorship or projects!
 Before I know it, it’s time to get the boys & the nightly activities began!!

Give yourself permission to change your grind if it’s not working for you. You have so many talents & gifts that you were given that you can use. Sometimes the traditional 9-5 grind isn’t for everyone and that’s ok. We thought it was for us and turns out, God had different plans for us…which were even better than we could have imagined.

The world needs your gifts! 
Share them!!

Always here to cheer you on!

Don’t give up.
Please don’t give up.
Yesterday was a reminder of why not giving up matters.
When we decided to go all in with our businesses & leave the classrooms, this was a little thing, that really is a big thing for us…time to hang out together on a weekday! To not have to wait for the weekends for a date night, in between sports 🙃🙃

This was the vision I had when people were questioning my side business. When people rolled their eyes or made small minded comments. This vision is what kept me going.
My passion & purpose has always been to be bigger than excuses or other people’s opinions. Yes, there have been hard days when I have thought, I could just give up. But would that serve my mission? No. There is always greatness on the other side of the hard. He always has a plan for us

 
I knew that if other women that I looked up to had created a life they loved, with time flexibility  then it was possible for anyone willing to put in the work 

 
Here’s the steps to take…
Keep your blinders on.
Create the life that works for you & your family.
Even if it’s nontraditional, as long as it matters to you & you’re making a difference, stay focused on your vision.
When you are clear on what sets your heart on fire, you’ll be motivated every day to make your dreams come true

If this hot mess mama could start my business with a 2 & 5 year old, while teaching full time, so can you!!
I will be here cheering you on the entire way, just please don’t give up on the life you want to live ❤️

It’s another favorite family Christmas tradition, but this year I added a Christmas spirit challenge. A few in the family laughed at me & maybe even gave an eye roll 🙄… but I promise even the teenager participated 🙌🏼 

🎄 smile at strangers 

🎄 give someone a compliment 

🎄hold the door open for others

🎄 let someone go ahead of you in line & say Merry Christmas❤️

Spreading the Christmas spirit was so fun! Weston said he was determined to win & he did! It doesn’t cost a thing, but our hope is that these challenges made each person feel the spirit of Christmas ❤️

I do wonder about this 🤣 shorts when it’s freezing 🥶 
At the same time I’m also incredibly blessed that his back is healed & healthy…there were many, many years where shoveling the driveway wasn’t an option. 

After 7 back surgeries and countless hours of rehabilitation and recovery ❤️‍🩹 forever grateful for these little wins!

Home for the holidays looks a little different this year & we’re ok with it ❤️🎄

Yesterday we kicked off our Christmas break with a morning workout with the fam bam, even Gram joined us!!!

“When everything feels like an uphill struggle, think of the view from the top.” — Unknown

This quote hits the ❤️…

Back in August we planned to surprise the boys with a vacation to our condo on Fort Myers Beach 🏝️ 

We planned to take advantage of their long Christmas break to explore the island and surrounding areas. 

Hurricane Ian changed all of our plans. 

It’s been a devastating 3 months of heartbreaking news for the island that we call our second home, lots of uphill struggles, but progress is being made 🙏🏼 and we’re continuing to pray for all the people on the island as they rebuild. 

When we got the notification that our condominium was inhabitable 💔, we decided to pivot our plans & head to spend Christmas with my parents.

Today’s hike was exactly what we needed…
Sunshine and the climb to the top to reflect. 

When life gives you struggles, take some time to reflect and know you will get through ❤️🙏🏼
Wishing you & your family a blessed Christmas Eve🙏🏼

Joy to the world, the Lord has come! 

Warmest wishes to everyone!! 

#merrychristmas #heisthereasonfortheseason

Tomorrow is a new year. And if I’m being honest, I have some new goals and announcements coming out in this New Year and they make me feel 😵‍💫 so I know it’s the right step in a new direction! 

Friends, life is so amazing. 
Live it every dang day. 
Set the goals that make you feel 😵‍💫 and run towards them. Because you are capable. Use your gifts + share them with others!! 

Happy New Year’s Eve!

It’s not about a number on the scale.
It’s not about restricting yourself from foods & drinks.
It’s not about a fad or a before & after. 

Coaching women with the total health solution is about…

Getting stronger physically & mentally.
Eating delicious foods that you love!! Even dessert every day 🧁
Learning how food helps your gut health. 
Joy, confidence and having an easy plan at home.
Investing less than $5 a day on yourself.
Being welcomed into a community of like minded women that will encourage, add value & motivate each other. 

Enrollment is now open & I couldn’t be more excited to share resources with you that help with your overall lifestyle!! 
Especially my simple habit tracker!! 

Grab the application in my bio or drop an emoji to be a part of this fulfillment ❤️

Remember to do what makes you feel alive ✨

Snow day = no school for the boys!! 

It’s always an exciting time & one that brings you back to your childhood memories 🥰

Unplugged from work this afternoon, just to enjoy this special gift 🎁 we were given today🙏🏼

These are the days we’ll remember!

Yes, that is a grown man in his 40’s going down the kiddy slide 🛝 at the airport at 1am 🤣

It’s a reminder how in every situation we have the choice of how to respond!!

As we were driving home from school the other day, I asked Weston if he wanted one of his parents to go on his school field trip, his first reply was, “sure, how about dad…he hasn’t been on a field trip in awhile.”

I agreed with his reasoning, but secretly wished he would have suggested me 💔

We drove for another 10 seconds and suddenly he shares, “actually, how about you come with?”

I quickly agreed with so much joy in my heart🥰

These were the days I used to wish for!! 
The thought of having the time flexibility within my work schedule was something I craved.
There were days when I wondered if it was possible…it took pushing the doubt aside & taking messy action💪🏼 

So today, I got up & was so excited!! We were suppose to be at the U of M Physics Force show, but the roof of the building collapsed!! 
Thank you Jesus for keeping everyone safe 🙏🏼

With the field trip being cancelled, we made a pivot.
Weston was bummed, but everything is figuroutable…next best alternative is having lunch together❤️

Here’s another reminder how life is filled with unknowns & we always have the choice of how we react!!

Jeffrey I love you so much & love celebrating the incredible person you are!

But they also questioned why they wouldn’t go for this opportunity to help other women fall in love with a healthy lifestyle, add another stream of income to their families & provide more travel opportunities!

These travel experiences are some of the greatest memories & in 31 days we’ll be together again 🏝️☀️

And bonus, there are new women that have partner with me this past year! We are all counting down the days (especially with all this snow coming), the message pod is blowing up & even the husbands have a text thread going!

This is truly one of the best trips that we earn each year because I get to see first hand the women on my team living in each other’s sunlight.

It is the best to see the hard work that these women have done over the past year & the fact that they get to bring a free guest, which most bring their husbands is also so special. 

It’s a time to witness the husbands so dang proud of their wives commitment to their goals and providing more opportunities for their families!! 

Let this be a reminder that each of us is capable of more. We all have moments of questioning ourselves. I’m seeing it right now with the new partners that are joining me! They are excited, maybe a little nervous, but going after their goals & figuring it out with their busy schedules. 

The key is…We just need to stick with people that feel like sunlight & even on the hardest days, borrow a little of their light to help us push through 🫶🏼

It’s not about the number on the scale.
It’s not about the number of calories or carbs.
It’s not about living with restrictions and shame.
It’s not about falling off the wagon & creating the never ending cycle over & over.

It’s about feeling proud of yourself.
It’s about celebrating the small wins.�It’s about eating food that is good for you & makes you feel good.

It’s about knowing that each minute, hour, day is a fresh start. 
It’s about fueling your mindset, because this changes our lives. 

My March Online Fitness & Wellness Group is officially starting on Monday & I’m locking arms with women that want a fresh start. Each day we will have a refreshing theme to give you tips & resources for a fresh start to create the lifestyle that you love & will sustain 🙌🏼

So excited for all the lives that will be impacted 🫶🏼

I believed I had an opportunity that could help her & her family.

At first she questioned if she could really take on one more thing.

I remember sharing with her how I was in a similar situation, but through opening my own wellness business I was starting to have something for me. Something that I looked forward to doing. Something that was helping others & also a new stream of income for my family. 

Sally decided to go for the opportunity & it’s been one of the most beautiful stories to watch unfold.
It’s come with a lot of consistency and work. When you see someone that is making dreams come true, know that it is only because they made the decision to make their dreams a priority & work towards them! 

Within a few years she reduced her teaching contract to part-time, to be home more with her kids.
Recently she moved into her dream home that has been on her vision board for over 6 years!!!
And today she made a last minute decision to surprise her family & bring them to Florida for spring break 🌴

Seeing women winning on my team is the BEST! 
And having their kids to share in the memories with is truly a gift that keeps giving. Hello leaving a legacy 🙌🏼

Today was once again a reminder to share, if you want something more in your life, go for it!!
If you have entertained the idea of changing something up in your life, go for it!
You get one shot at this life, live the heck out of it!! 

BODi does not guarantee any level of success or income from the Partnership Opportunity. Each Partner’s income depends on his or her own efforts, diligence, and skill.

So much makes sense now!
This morning as I was getting ready to volunteer at church I had this podcast on. 

I’ve often questioned why some people seem to just go through the motions of life and act like they don’t have choices or much happiness. While others, are filled with life & happiness.

Trust me, I’ve been on both sides of this coin too…

This podcast is a must listen, Mel Robbins breaks it down in this metaphor is brilliant…that life is like a road trip. 

Are you the driver or the passenger of your life?
Are you even on the right road? 
Do you need to pick a new direction? 
Are you heading where you want to go, but speeding so fast you can’t enjoy the ride?
Is it time to update the road trip playlist (in your head)?
And most importantly, what lies on the road ahead? 

Aren’t these SO good!!!!!

She also shared how research proves that scheduling stops along the road of life to look forward to that bring you joy are necessary. 

For example a trip, a time to volunteer, time with yourself. Whatever makes you happy. Something you look forward to. 

This makes so much sense now…often in my business I’m looking forward to the next live event, team call, or team vacation! There is always something coming up that lies ahead filled with the best days yet to come!! Today when I heard this, I caught myself feeling blessed because each day I’m truly loving this life. 

Yes, even with life’s challenges, the love for mentoring women each day is beyond a blessing & to do life with so many uplifting women is a true gift 🙏🏼 that I want every women to feel during this short trip of life. 

I’ll drop the link of the podcast below for you! 
If you’ve felt blah in your life, give this message some thought. Give yourself permission to change the direction of your journey, you’re in the drivers seat babe!! 🫶🏼

@melrobbins

The thought of taking a spring break trip to an all inclusive resort 8 years ago was just that…a thought. I remember teaching and hearing the excitement from the students in my class that were getting ready to travel to Mexico. I was excited for them, but was also envious. 

I wanted to travel! Especially by this time of the year in MN when winter seems never ending 😩. 

I wanted to see more of the world with Jeff and travel together, but it wasn’t something we could fit in our budget.

I sat with settling for a few years…and realized that wasn’t getting me anywhere. I could feel that there was more opportunities out there for me, I just had to find them.

It was when I saw my friend traveling. She was talking about earning her trip. Again I thought, good for her, but then I thought if she could make this happen, could I? 

I let these thoughts live in my mind for awhile and finally called her. I asked her about her online wellness business. My main question was time…how much time does this business take you to do each day?

She replied, at first about an hour or two a day. 

I talked with Jeff. He was so encouraging, he said, “babe, you can do that.” I let fear creep into my mind with excuses…”what about the boys? When would I fit this in?” Jeff simply said, “you’ll make it work.”

He was right. 

When something is a priority, you make it work. 
When it’s not a priority, you let it pass. 

From the first day of opening this wellness business I have made it work. 
From working in the car pick up line to the sidelines of baseball practice, I have made this work because it’s work that matters. 

I have learned that if you want something bad enough in life, you have to put in the work. Even on the busy days, they all count!

From the consistent work, we’re now enjoying our 13th all inclusive vacation and I am forever grateful for this gift. I’m also forever grateful to share this gift with so many other women that earned it too!! 

If we can do this, so can you! 
I’m inviting you to join my newsletter where I will share the details of how you can get started and be here next year 🏝️🫶🏼 

Drop a ❤️ and I’ll send it over🫶🏼
These people, these experiences, this life just keeps getting better & better 🙏🏼❤️

It’s what you don’t see in these pictures that matters the MOST.

Yes, vacationing in paradise is truly amazing, but this business is so much more.

It’s the conversations around the pool that you don’t get to hear/see about, so let me go there for you.

The conversations are about making the decision to go after the life we want to live. To end the generational pattern of one career. To provide more in your life with people you WANT to do life with. To show your children that it is possible to have a 9-5 and also have another business that adds people in your life who YOU choose to do life with, who bring out the best in you!

It’s the confidence that shines through from the former perfectionist. The women that used to always worried about what others would think, but now know, it’s only important of what you think of yourself & the life you want to live. 

These women are so much more than business partners. 

We pray for each other. 
We cry for each other. 
We laugh with each other.
We travel with each other. 
We workout with each other. 
We randomly reach out and thank each other just because. 
We have connected our husbands together.
We have paved new roads for our families. 

When I started this business I NEVER knew any of this was possible. I was just going through the daily grind of life, knowing there was more out there…I never had this on my radar, but that is the beauty of all of it. One of the most impactful decisions I made 8 years ago, was never in my life plans. God placed this on my heart to try. He has great plans for all of us, when we try. 

So as I reflect on this amazing vacation and all the conversations, I know this team & our mission is to welcome more women that feel the tug on their heart to go for this and be a part of something bigger than you can imagine! Because many of the conversations from these moments were about you! Thinking of sharing this life with you too 🫶🏼

Love you forever 🫶🏼
Home is wherever you are.

The struggle used to be real…
Literally trudging through the day teaching, watching the clock because I was addicted to Diet Coke. I needed that pick me up by lunch. Then another in the afternoon before daycare pick up. Then another with dinner. It was an exhausting cycle. 
Then add the confusion on top of this with all the “healthy messages.”
The catchy marketing (low fat, no sugar, 100 calories, no carb).
And looking back on it, there are so many catchy messages out there about eating healthy, it’s hard to know what is best.

I was desperate for a change. But it had to be manageable. 
I can confidently say, 8 years ago the struggle stopped.
With a 3 week program, one that I was skeptical of, totally changed my life.

I finally learned how to eat. Turns out many women are not eating enough.
I finally learned how about portions and how much of each food group to eat.
I finally learned that restrictions are not the answer.
I finally learned that living a healthy lifestyle doesn’t need to be complicated.

This literally changed everything for me + my family.
For over 8 years I have been mentoring busy mamas and sharing resources to help them too.
And it just keeps getting better, because tomorrow is a new day one!

Tomorrow I’m kicking off the month with an updated 3 week plan that is focusing on simple nutrition, workouts + mindset work! We’re having coffee chats online, a private online group to collaborate in & fun!!!

My initial 21 spots filled up, and I don’t have the heart to make any women wait 🫶🏼 so I’m keeping enrollment open for the next two days! Give a ❤️ or drop an emoji in the comments! 

This will be enough time to get you caught up and started with us!

Happiness comes in many forms. 

Happiness today was getting in a killer workout with my hubs & ending with a little dance 💃🏼 sesh😂

Bringing the boys to school, meeting an amazing friend at the cutest coffee shop @thefoxandpantry and walking the aisle of Target 🎯 without ever having to look at the time. 

It’s the little moments that can bring so much happiness 🙏🏼

“He is not here; He has risen, just as He said.” Matthew 28:6

Happy Easter 🙏🏼 
May you experience miracles each day.

If we waited until we had the time or until we had all of the boxes checked ✔️ to build our businesses, we would still be waiting. We would still be going through the grind of the day, wishing & hoping for more of a change. 

The secret is to make the time. 
To invest your time & money so that you can start to build your dreams now. 

There is never the perfect time to start. 
We all have a million excuses. 

When I started I had a husband that was working three jobs. 
We had two little boys in daycare & preschool. 
We only had time to hang out as a family on the weekend, if we were lucky.
And the debt (school loans) just seemed to always be hanging around. 

I used my circumstances as my WHY for starting my side business because I wanted a “yes” life! 

Looking back, making the time when I was “super busy” continues to change our lives. 
Even if it’s these little date days that we can unplug, hit up a quick coffee date @kingdomcoffeemn have chocolate 🍫 hanging out on my teeth 😂 & enjoying this 80 degree day!! 

The best part…It’s available for you too.
Make the time.

Next week my mama turns 70 years old 🎉 & she continues to prove that age is just a number!! 

Yesterday she joined our women’s walking crew and once we got back asked if we could go lift!!

Knowing the major benefits of strength training for women, I was all for it!

Strength training isn’t just for bodybuilders or athletes; it’s a powerful tool for pre-menopausal women to enhance their overall health and well-being. As women approach menopause, they experience hormonal changes that can lead to muscle loss, bone density reduction, and weight gain. Engaging in regular strength training exercises can provide a multitude of benefits, both physically and mentally, during this transitional phase of life!! 

Sharing the 3 perks of strength training with you: 

1. Preserving Muscle Mass: Strength training helps combat age-related muscle loss, known as sarcopenia, by stimulating muscle growth and maintenance. This can improve overall strength, making everyday activities easier to perform.

2. Increasing Bone Density: As estrogen levels decline during menopause, bone density can decrease, leading to an increased risk of osteoporosis. Strength training puts stress on the bones, promoting bone remodeling and increasing bone density, reducing the risk of fractures.

3. Managing Weight: Metabolism tends to slow down during menopause, making it easier to gain weight. Strength training boosts the resting metabolic rate, helping to burn more calories even at rest and aiding in weight management.

How powerful are these perks!?!

In today’s fast-paced world, finding time for self-care can be challenging, especially for women in their 40s who often juggle multiple responsibilities. However, one simple and accessible activity can make a world of difference in their overall well-being: daily walking. Let’s explore the remarkable benefits of this age-friendly exercise routine.

1. Enhanced Physical Health 💪🏼
Regular walking can be a game-changer for women in their 40s. It helps improve cardiovascular health, lower blood pressure, and reduce the risk of chronic diseases like heart disease, diabetes, and stroke. As women enter their 40s, these health concerns become increasingly important, making walking a valuable preventative measure.

Weight Management 🩷
Maintaining a healthy weight can become more challenging with age, but daily walking can help. It burns calories, boosts metabolism, and promotes muscle tone. Combined with a balanced diet, walking can support weight management goals and boost self-confidence.

Mood and Stress Reduction🥹
Women in their 40s often face a variety of stressors, from career demands to family responsibilities. Daily walking is a natural stress reliever, triggering the release of endorphins that can help improve mood and reduce anxiety. It provides a peaceful break from the hustle and bustle of daily life.

Turning my mess into a message…

I’m a firm believer that often times the messiness of life can happen for us, not to us.  That we can use the mess to share & help others…

For several months I have been experiencing weight gain, fatigue, brain fog, hair loss & just out of sorts 🤪

Life had been crazy with preparing to move our lives across the country, selling our house in MN, packing, traveling, getting settled in a new state…the list goes on & on…so I was trying to take these big life changes into consideration, but my health concerns were still hanging around after getting settled & I knew I had to do something.

After tapping into a few resources, I discovered the opportunity to study women’s health through a Cycle Syncing Course. 

I enrolled in the certification program & got busy diving into the different course content in hopes that it would help me. 

It covered hormone health, syncing your workouts & food with your cycles, adrenal fatigue, cortisol levels, sleep, moon syncing…seriously SO MUCH great information!! It’s really mind blowing how much information is out there to help us, we just have to know what we’re looking for.

Women 35+ want to incorporate strength training into their routine. There are so many benefits. Here’s 3:

1. Preserving Muscle Mass: Strength training helps combat age-related muscle loss, known as sarcopenia, by stimulating muscle growth and maintenance. This can improve overall strength, making everyday activities easier to perform.

2. Increasing Bone Density: As estrogen levels decline during menopause, bone density can decrease, leading to an increased risk of osteoporosis. Strength training puts stress on the bones, promoting bone remodeling and increasing bone density, reducing the risk of fractures.

3. Managing Weight: Metabolism tends to slow down during menopause, making it easier to gain weight. Strength training boosts the resting metabolic rate, helping to burn more calories even at rest and aiding in weight management.

Hey ladies! Let’s dive into the wonderful world of Zone 2 workouts and why they’re a game-changer for us on our fitness journey! 🏃‍♀️💫

* Fat Burning Focus: Zone 2 workouts target that sweet spot where your body burns fat for fuel. Yup, you heard it right! It’s like having a personal fat-burning engine revved up during these sessions. 🚀🔥 
* Building Endurance & Stamina: Training in Zone 2 helps improve endurance without feeling wiped out. It’s all about building that stamina for the long haul, whether it’s running, cycling, or any cardio activity. 🚴‍♀️⏱️ 
* Balanced Recovery: Working out in this zone isn’t just about pushing hard—it’s about finding a balance. It allows your body to recover while still making progress, reducing the risk of burnout or overtraining. 🧘‍♀️🌟 
* Heart Health Boost: Zone 2 workouts are a fantastic way to strengthen your heart. They help improve cardiovascular health by training your heart to be more efficient, lowering resting heart rate, and enhancing overall heart function. ❤️🏋️‍♀️ 
* Stress Relief & Mental Clarity: These workouts aren’t just about physical gains! They also give your mind a breather, reducing stress and boosting mental clarity. It’s like hitting refresh for your entire system! 🧠🌈 
So, if you’re aiming for fat loss, improved endurance, a healthier heart, and a clearer mind, Zone 2 workouts might just be your secret weapon! Mix it up, find your groove, and enjoy the incredible benefits! 🙌💃
